# PCI Compliance Standard

## Purpose

Define Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard (PCI DSS) requirements for the enterprise e-commerce platform using Stripe.

Goal: maintain **SAQ A** (Self-Assessment Questionnaire A) eligibility — the lowest PCI scope for merchants who outsource card processing.

---

## PCI Scope

### In Scope (Managed by Stripe)

- Card number collection
- Card storage (tokenization)
- Card transmission to payment networks
- 3D Secure authentication

### Out of Scope (Our Responsibility)

- Application security protecting checkout page
- HTTPS on checkout pages
- Not handling card data on our servers
- Secure webhook handling
- Access control to systems near checkout

### Never in Our Environment

- Primary Account Number (PAN)
- Card Verification Value (CVV/CVC/CVC2/CVV2)
- Full magnetic stripe data
- PIN blocks

If any of these touch our servers, SAQ A is lost and full PCI DSS applies.

---

## SAQ A Requirements

SAQ A applies when:

- All payment processing outsourced to Stripe
- Only Stripe JavaScript (Elements) collects card data
- Card data goes directly from browser to Stripe
- Our servers never see, store, or transmit PAN

Our checkout page loads Stripe.js and Payment Element — card fields are Stripe-hosted iframes.

---

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend

```typescript
// CORRECT: Stripe Payment Element
const stripe = await loadStripe(publishableKey);
const elements = stripe.elements({ clientSecret });
const paymentElement = elements.create("payment");
paymentElement.mount("#payment-element");

// WRONG: Custom card input
<input name="cardNumber" />  // NEVER DO THIS
```

Rules:

- Use `@stripe/stripe-js` and `@stripe/react-stripe-js`
- Use Payment Element or Checkout — not deprecated Card Element for new integrations
- Load Stripe.js from `https://js.stripe.com` only — never self-host
- Publishable key (`pk_`) only in frontend — safe to expose

### Backend

```python
# CORRECT: Create PaymentIntent, return client_secret
intent = stripe.PaymentIntent.create(amount=amount, currency="usd", ...)
return {"client_secret": intent.client_secret}

# WRONG: Accept card number in API
class PaymentRequest(BaseModel):
    card_number: str  # NEVER
    cvv: str          # NEVER
```

Rules:

- Secret key (`sk_`) only on server
- Never log PaymentIntent responses containing sensitive fields
- Webhook signature verification mandatory

